headline.main: BOMBERS NEEDED FOR MIDDLE EAST; Britain Has Been Handicapped by Insufficient Force to Demolish Axis Targets SUPPLY LINES NOT CLOSED Germans, in Greece, Crete and Rhodes, Menace Entire Suez Canal District

lead_paragraph: CAIRO, Egypt, Sept. 28 -- A first-hand view of the battle of supplies, the part that heavy bombers are playing in it, and the general strategic situation forces upon one the conviction that the British are not out of the woods yet in the Eastern Mediterranean despite the respite given by Germany's invasion of Russia.
abstract: Brit efforts to halt Axis supplies for north Africa, lack of bombers and work of Fleet Air Arm and RAF discussed
